<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-30T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-30T18:00:00-05:00" n="224" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/1752: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-30T18:00:00-05:00">November 30, 1933—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>100. Our 97, November 27 [<hi rend="italic">26</hi>], noon.<note n="52" xml:id="d224fn52">Not printed.</note> Despite repeated efforts
                            Dawson has been unable to see Olaya, but his private secretary told
                            Dawson that the President would sign the debt bill before tomorrow
                            evening. President would, however, point out at the same time the
                            advisability of Congress in its next session amending the act in certain
                            particulars.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>